sentences: Vashtie Kola (often stylized as Va$htie; born April 23, 1981) is an American music video director, filmmaker, artist, designer, creative consultant and disc jockey.
She has been active in the downtown New York City scene for over a decade.
She moved to New York City in 1999 to attend the School of Visual Arts, where she studied film.
She graduated in 2004.
In 2005, Kola was signed to Box Fresh Pictures as a director alongside Anthony Mandler.
Kola was asked to re-vamp the company of Island Def Jam as director of creative services in 2006.
That year Kola also started an monthly '90s party with her friend Oscar Sanchez called "1992".

The following year, Vibe listed the "31 Most Stylish People Under 31" with Kola coming in at 23rd.

In this year, Kola was interviewed Sean "Diddy" Combs for Supreme Magazine, which was photographed by Terry Richardson, and was included in the Nike Destroyer Campaign alongside Dee & Ricky and Scott Campbell.
